132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1896
H.P. 1267 House of Representatives, May 5, 2025
Resolve, to Support Pro Se Litigants Regarding the Return Receipt
of Service
Received by the Clerk of the House on May 1, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Judiciary pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative WARREN of Scarborough.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Judicial Department to amend rules. Resolved: That the Judicial
2 Department shall amend the Maine Rules of Civil Procedure, Rule 4 to permit return receipt
3 of service by electronic means.
4 SUMMARY
55 This resolve requires the Judicial Department to amend the Maine Rules of Civil
66 Procedure, Rule 4 to permit return receipt of service by electronic means.
